snippet.textDisplay: I have this song on repeat everyday. I love Lamb of God. Love every album by them.  and will always be a huge fan. I love Randy's calm singing voice in the beginning and near the end. It gives me goosebumps everytime and his screams... Fucking amazing. The lyrics are so dark, but describe my life and story well. Willie and Mark kill it at those badass guitar riffs. John's bass is dead on, accurate, and can hear it really  good. Art Cruz will never be a Chris Atler, but he was the perfect replacement for the drummer of the band. I love Art's twist too the drums!!

Not only have we gotten one of the BIGGEST comic book movie crossovers with Marvel's Avengers Endgame, but now thanks to Lamb of God, we're finally getting to see Mathew Perry from Friends square off against Pennywise the dancing clown. (Except he's in female form now.) yeaaa idk why either.

Maybe I interpreted that all wrong. This could just be another fucking game in the series of Mortal Kombat with Johnny Cage vs Mileena. Fuck idk anymore!

AWESOME LYRICS:

By the darkest river, beneath the leafless trees
I think I’m drowning, this dream is killing me
In the coldest winter, between the fading lights
I feel I’m falling into a frozen sky
Past the blackest heaven, above the dying stars
I watch me breaking into a million shards
But through the hardest hour, below the cruelest sign
I know I’m waking up from this wretched lie
Wake up

A depression fed by overload
False perceptions, the weight of the world
A universe in the palm of your hand
The artifice of endless strands

Distraction flows down an obsessive stream
Rejection grows into oppressive screams

The hardest hour, the cruelest sign
I’m waking up from this wretched lie
I fight it the same, don’t waste this day
Wake up, wake up, wake up
Memento mori

The regression of advancing modes
And Imperial corrosive nodes
A prime directive to disconnect
Reclaim yourself and resurrect

Distraction flows down an obsessive stream
Rejection grows into oppressive screams

The hardest hour, the cruelest sign
I’m waking up from this wretched lie
I fight it the same, don’t waste this day
Wake up, wake up, wake up
Memento mori

And I hear their relentless voices
But you’ve gotta run them out
Return to now and shut it down (shut it down)

Because there’s too many choices
